summary: I don’t think they consider YouTube as their employer specifically but they have said on numerous occasions that they consider...
question: I don’t think they consider YouTube as their employer specifically but they have said on numerous occasions that they consider google as their employer (still doesn’t detract that it’s icky and they should’ve have done it)
answer: Yeah, they have said that, but in reality their relationship is very unlike your typical employer/employee relationship, and Dan and Phil have a lot of power in that relationship. I will be interested to see if they do the youtube rewind again, especially since their last time caused so much negativity in the community of other youtubers.

summary: Ok I know the try guys are the main cause for concern, but what about YouTube last year on their post for rewind where they,...
question: Ok I know the try guys are the main cause for concern, but what about YouTube last year on their post for rewind where they, YOUTUBE THE COMPANY, queerbaited and used dnps relationship as a selling point. How crap must that feel to them, having their relationship reduced to a punchline by their OWN EMPLOYERS?? WTF?? Not only to other creators "sell" their relationship, but their employers do too. It's so disgusting. ('In a relationship with ... YouTube rewind' dnp were the 1st photo)
answer: I don’t think Dan and Phil consider YouTube their employer, but I agree that it’s icky. But I do think that probably Dan and Phil have more control over what YouTube officially posts, or at least hey can ask them to take it down. But I actually have no idea how they feel about it.
